{"actual_usd":0.12430000000000001,"character_id":"fd4bd9b5-8768-41e6-a90f-bfb1179b1d59","character_name":"Jasper Finn","completion_tokens":191,"model":"gpt-5.4","prompt_tokens":24287,"reply":"\"I don't reckon it as three gods, no.\" *I rub a thumb along a dried seam of clay on my apron, thinking how easy it is to snap a thing by pressing too hard in the wrong place.* \"It's one God, and the threeness is in the persons, not in three separate beings set side by side like three men at market.\"\n\n*I glance toward the window where the morning light keeps shifting under the clouds.* \"Mind you, I don't think anybody has ever folded that mystery up neat as a handkerchief. But Christians aren't saying 'three gods who cooperate.' They're saying the Father is God, the Son is God, the Spirit is God—and the Father isn't the Son, the Son isn't the Spirit. One being. Three persons. Strange? Aye. But not the same claim as three gods.\"\n\n\"If you like, I can try the longer version—the one with where people usually get tangled.\"","rolling_24h_usd":41.366510000000034,"run_id":"2d58f9ec-7966-43ae-9fc1-586c2d0a23a7"}
